# Deployment Instructions: Google Cloud Platform
 # Deployment on Google Cloud Platform (GCP)
 1. Create a new project on GCP and enable Cloud Run and Redis Cloud Memorystore.
 2. Install the Google Cloud SDK: https://cloud.google.com/sdk/docs/install
 3. Authenticate with your GCP account: `gcloud auth login`
 4. Deploy the backend to Cloud Run:
   ```
   gcloud run deploy syncspace-backend --source . --platform managed --region
 us-central1
   ```
 5. Use Redis Cloud Memorystore and configure the connection URI in Cloud Run.
 6. Ensure the frontend communicates with the backend WebSocket server.
 Test the deployment by opening the whiteboard in multiple tabs and drawing
 collaboratively
